1
00:00:02,520 --> 00:00:04,860
-: Next thing that I want to work on here

2
00:00:04,860 --> 00:00:07,620
is when we are working with product,

3
00:00:07,620 --> 00:00:12,060
we need an association between product and category.

4
00:00:12,060 --> 00:00:17,060
If we go to category, it is action, sci-fi, and history.

5
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:19,620
Basically any product that we have

6
00:00:19,620 --> 00:00:22,800
will belong to one of the category.

7
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:25,050
So that will be a foreign key relation

8
00:00:25,050 --> 00:00:28,500
between product and category table.

9
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:32,310
How can we accomplish that with EF Core?

10
00:00:32,310 --> 00:00:34,650
Now, if we did not have EF Core,

11
00:00:34,650 --> 00:00:37,830
we will basically have a column of category ID

12
00:00:37,830 --> 00:00:39,870
in the product table and then,

13
00:00:39,870 --> 00:00:42,420
we will have a constraint on foreign key,

14
00:00:42,420 --> 00:00:45,750
which we will add in SQL server.

15
00:00:45,750 --> 00:00:48,300
But thankfully because of EF Core,

16
00:00:48,300 --> 00:00:51,000
we do not have to touch our database.

17
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:55,260
All we have to do is define some constraint in our model

18
00:00:55,260 --> 00:01:00,064
and entity framework will take care of everything else.

19
00:01:00,064 --> 00:01:04,200
So how can we accomplish that foreign key relation

20
00:01:04,200 --> 00:01:07,140
between category and product?

21
00:01:07,140 --> 00:01:09,330
Let me close all the tab here

22
00:01:09,330 --> 00:01:14,330
and let me open the model here, which is product model.

23
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:19,080
There we basically need a column for category ID.

24
00:01:19,080 --> 00:01:24,080
So prop integer, I will call that category ID.

25
00:01:24,450 --> 00:01:27,960
Now if I add just this column, table will not

26
00:01:27,960 --> 00:01:32,550
know that this is a foreign key to the category table.

27
00:01:32,550 --> 00:01:35,070
In order to explicitly define that,

28
00:01:35,070 --> 00:01:39,660
we need a navigation property to the category table.

29
00:01:39,660 --> 00:01:43,740
So right here, we will have a navigation property

30
00:01:43,740 --> 00:01:47,973
to category table and I will call that category.

31
00:01:48,960 --> 00:01:52,107
And on top of that we have to explicitly define

32
00:01:52,107 --> 00:01:56,040
that this category property is used for foreign

33
00:01:56,040 --> 00:01:59,760
key navigation for the category ID.

34
00:01:59,760 --> 00:02:03,420
And for that we have a data annotation of foreign

35
00:02:03,420 --> 00:02:07,260
key and we can say that this category table has

36
00:02:07,260 --> 00:02:12,003
a foreign key which will be category ID, right here.

37
00:02:12,840 --> 00:02:14,940
That is all that we have to write.

38
00:02:14,940 --> 00:02:17,040
And then entity framework core

39
00:02:17,040 --> 00:02:20,073
will take care of everything else.

40
00:02:21,090 --> 00:02:25,503
So you can see how powerful entity framework core really is.

41
00:02:26,700 --> 00:02:29,520
With that configured, let me save that

42
00:02:29,520 --> 00:02:31,503
and I will add a migration.

43
00:02:32,760 --> 00:02:34,950
So we will add a migration

44
00:02:34,950 --> 00:02:37,260
and I will call that add foreign key

45
00:02:37,260 --> 00:02:39,663
for category product relation.

46
00:02:40,980 --> 00:02:43,890
Now when you change anything with the core model,

47
00:02:43,890 --> 00:02:46,410
if it requires a database change,

48
00:02:46,410 --> 00:02:48,615
entity framework core is smart enough

49
00:02:48,615 --> 00:02:51,390
and it does all of that.

50
00:02:51,390 --> 00:02:54,000
You can see it is adding a column here

51
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:56,760
and it is updating some data.

52
00:02:56,760 --> 00:02:59,130
But when it is updating the data,

53
00:02:59,130 --> 00:03:01,470
you can see it is setting all the value

54
00:03:01,470 --> 00:03:04,950
to be zero for category ID.

55
00:03:04,950 --> 00:03:09,334
That is not what we want because we are seeding our data

56
00:03:09,334 --> 00:03:14,334
we need to actually pass category in that seed data.

57
00:03:14,520 --> 00:03:16,920
So this migration that got added,

58
00:03:16,920 --> 00:03:20,340
I am not happy with it because I am going to change

59
00:03:20,340 --> 00:03:24,810
something in the seed data and create a new migration.

60
00:03:24,810 --> 00:03:28,140
Now, only because this migration has not been

61
00:03:28,140 --> 00:03:29,940
pushed to the database,

62
00:03:29,940 --> 00:03:34,530
I can directly come here and we can go to migrations

63
00:03:34,530 --> 00:03:36,513
and delete that migration.

64
00:03:37,530 --> 00:03:40,200
You do not want to do that directly here.

65
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:42,420
You can go to package manager

66
00:03:42,420 --> 00:03:45,900
and you can write the command, remove migration

67
00:03:45,900 --> 00:03:49,443
and it'll remove the last migration that was added.

68
00:03:51,406 --> 00:03:53,940
You can see in the migrations folder

69
00:03:53,940 --> 00:03:58,263
that migration does not exist anymore and it got removed.

70
00:03:59,910 --> 00:04:02,460
So now we can add a new migration.

71
00:04:02,460 --> 00:04:06,690
But before we do that, we have to fix our seed data

72
00:04:06,690 --> 00:04:09,840
that is inside application DB context.

73
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:13,470
Here we have to pass a category ID.

74
00:04:13,470 --> 00:04:15,750
You can pass anything you want.

75
00:04:15,750 --> 00:04:18,420
I am going to be random about it.

76
00:04:18,420 --> 00:04:20,850
Some of them I will say one.

77
00:04:20,850 --> 00:04:24,510
The other one I will say two here,

78
00:04:24,510 --> 00:04:26,943
and last one, I will say three.

79
00:04:28,590 --> 00:04:29,580
So perfect.

80
00:04:29,580 --> 00:04:33,390
We have assigned some value to the category ID

81
00:04:33,390 --> 00:04:35,070
and when we are seeding,

82
00:04:35,070 --> 00:04:38,820
make sure that you use the category ID that exists

83
00:04:38,820 --> 00:04:41,700
and not something random like 11.

84
00:04:41,700 --> 00:04:43,053
That will not work.

85
00:04:44,190 --> 00:04:47,820
With that configured, let me go to package manager

86
00:04:47,820 --> 00:04:50,883
